Diagnosis:
This species can be recognized by the shape of surstyli in dorsal view, right surstylus quadratic-shaped with small inner projection, left surstylus elongated, rather rectangular-shaped, longer than right one (
Fig. 39A
); epandrium wider than long, slightly ovate-shaped (
Fig. 39A
); phallus trifid with wavy ejaculatory ducts (
Fig. 39D–E
); asymmetrical gonopods in ventral view, right higher than left one (
Fig. 39B
); hypandrium ovate-shaped with distinct hypandrial apodeme in ventral view (
Fig. 39B
).
